OL,3,CResidents patrolling streets as anti-
OL,4,Csocial bike riding becoming 'the norm'
OL,6,FCllr Shakeel Hussain, who represents
OL,7,Fthe Ropner ward, said: "It was a local
OL,8,Fthing, but now we've seen that it is
OL,9,Fspreading across the borough and it's
OL,10,Fbecoming the norm. If we ignore it, it
OL,11,Fwill get worse, it probably will
OL,12,Fbecome a lawless society."
OL,14,FMeanwhile, the issue has been raised
OL,15,Fin parliament today by a North East MP.
